The '''National Rehabilitation Hospital (NRH)''' in [[Dún Laoghaire]], Dublin, is an Irish publicly funded hospital that provides rehabilitation treatment for patients who have a physical or cognitive disability due to illness or injury.<ref>{{cite news|author=Elaine Edwards |url=http://www.irishtimes.com/news/health/national-rehabilitation-hospital-120-bed-unit-to-get-15m-1.2314710 |title=National Rehabilitation Hospital 120-bed unit to get €15m |publisher=Irishtimes.com |date=2015-08-12 |accessdate=2017-05-14}}</ref> Although it is funded by the state the hospital is owned by a [[Catholic religious order]], the [[Sisters of Mercy]].<ref>{{cite news|author=Paul Cullen |url=http://www.irishtimes.com/news/health/q-a-what-s-the-story-with-religious-orders-owning-hospitals-1.3054256 |title=Q&A: What’s the story with religious orders owning hospitals? |publisher=Irishtimes.com |date=2017-04-20 |accessdate=2017-05-14}}</ref>

The [[Health Service Executive]] has been criticised for staff shortages at the hospital which caused twelve beds to be unavailable in March 2017 in spite of a waiting list of over 200 patients seeking admission.<ref>{{cite news|author=Ruairi Cotter |url=https://www.thesun.ie/news/654261/twelve-beds-lying-empty-at-the-national-rehabilitation-hospital-despite-a-waiting-list-of-226-patients/ |title=Twelve beds lying empty at the National Rehabilitation Hospital despite a waiting list of 226 patients |publisher=Thesun.ie |date=2017-03-01 |accessdate=2017-05-14}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.independent.ie/irish-news/health/over-200-brain-and-spinal-patients-face-agonising-wait-as-beds-closed-35607222.html |title=Over 200 brain and spinal patients face agonising wait as beds closed |publisher=Independent.ie |date=2017-04-09 |accessdate=2017-05-14}}</ref> The hospital has a total of 110 beds but is said to be under-resourced according to advocacy organisation ''An Soal'' as well as senior staff of the hospital.<ref>{{cite news|author=Kitty Holland |url=http://www.irishtimes.com/news/social-affairs/families-of-brain-injury-survivors-being-given-no-hope-1.2762159 |title=Families of brain injury survivors being given ‘no hope’ |publisher=Irishtimes.com |date=2016-08-20 |accessdate=2017-05-14}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|author=Laura Lynott |url=http://www.herald.ie/news/we-have-56-beds-in-neuro-rehab-but-we-really-need-280-35444928.html |title='We have 56 beds in neuro rehab... but we really need 280' |publisher=Herald.ie |date=2017-02-13 |accessdate=2017-05-14}}</ref> Funding for an additional 120 beds was approved in 2015.<ref>{{cite news|author=Fiona Dillon |url=http://www.herald.ie/news/national-rehabilitation-hospital-to-get-new-15m-120bed-revamp-31445303.html |title=National Rehabilitation Hospital to get new €15m 120-bed revamp |publisher=Herald.ie |date=2015-08-12 |accessdate=2017-05-14}}</ref>

